This is Perl module Try::Simple.

INSTALLATION

Type the following command:

    $ curl -L http://cpanmin.us | perl - Try::Simple

Or install cpanm and then run the following command to install
Try::Simple:

    $ cpanm Try::Simple

If you get an archive of this distribution, unpack it and build it
as per the usual:

    $ tar xzf Try-Simple-$version.tar.gz
    $ cd Try-Simple-$version
    $ perl Build.PL
    $ ./Build && ./Build test

Then install it:

    $ ./Build install

DOCUMENTATION

Try::Simple documentation is available as in POD. So you can do:

    $ perldoc Try::Simple

to read the documentation online with your favorite pager.

